Use the quotient rule  a^m / a^n = a^{m-n}.  If the resulting exponent is negative, rewrite it in the denominator (or numerator) so that the exponent is positive.

a) (-3t)^2 / (-3t)^8  
   = (-3t)^{2-8}  
   = (-3t)^{-6}  
   = 1 / (-3t)^6

b) f^{47} / (f^{49} · f)  
   = f^{47} / f^{50}          (since f^{49}·f = f^{49+1}=f^{50})  
   = f^{47-50}  
   = f^{-3}  
   = 1 / f^{3}

c) (2 k^{4}) / (5 k^{7})  
   = (2/5) · k^{4-7}  
   = (2/5) · k^{-3}  
   = 2 / (5 k^{3})

Thus:

a) 1 / (−3t)^6  
b) 1 / f^3  
c) 2 / (5 k^3)
